<br />

<br />
That'd work for some stuff, but overall, I think 5 levels is about right.  10 levels trivializes so much content.  Just think of the impact of 10 levels on getting to Elementals and Time.  You can't Vox/Naggy that yet.  No, I like 5 levels at a time.  It's some levels, but not too many.  It is some new changes, but not big ones that can cause all sorts of problems.  It makes content easier for those just doing it, but not too much so.  It means more content designed for that 5 level increment, rather than it spread out over 10.  Basically, more quality instead of a need for quantity.
<br />

<br />
I do wish they'd Naggy'd and Vox'd more stuff, but that really requires a proper use of required level.  Not recommended...required.  If crap had required levels, standards for various levels of gear could be maintained and raids could offer the best stuff for people in their level range.  But that's not the case and LDoN makes the big mistake of going all out with the ineffective recommended as opposed to the effective required.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
