I think the idea of class specification and being able to branch off would be cool. The specialiations try to do that but the effect they hold is so miniscul its nearly pointless to compair our class based on that. But that idea I really love.
<br />

<br />
In regards to some of the topics placed forth, my thoughts &gt;&lt; :
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Enchanter Animations vs other pet casters (especially pet focus items).... why dont we have these? </span> 
<br />

<br />
I think we get like gimp class pet cause we can always charm something, mind you not everything is charmable but when we do get a good mob, just make everyone else drool. TT Getting the added animation empathy as an AA was a big step. We can at least control the buggers now. I still find them infinately useful for farming and the like. 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Charm and LDON, why are so much of the dungeons flagged immune? </span> 
<br />

<br />
We can charm in most of the dungeons, im still unconfirmed with Mirgs. In Guk we have eyes, Mistmoore I blieve we can charm the mummies ( i haven been their in a while). They did put in a new mob flag change making the shadows summoned beings and the rats flagged as animals now. Can anyone find out if these make them charmable now? In Ruj the wolves charm, and tak the summoned "rockthings" (I win in remembering names today). Hasted they make for some serious dps. Definitly in hard. Pets hitting on averge 900 - 988 in hard. &lt;3 it.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Direcharm, worthless in LDON? Please throw in some direcharm bait.. </span>
<br />

<br />
:/ level 65 i have not seen anything DC'able. Lvl 60s may have better luck finding mobs 45+ if they have lower group lvls but SOE has seemed to keep up with keeping  the avg lvl of mobs near the group. Time to /feedback for at least one dc'able pet in each dungeon.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Recipes and Tradeskills, useful stuff worth making and selling W R U? </span> 
<br />

<br />
With so many people picking up tradeskills for platters and earrings seems you cant find anything you can make in mass quantities any more that sells well. Even cultrual armor is getting replaced with ornate and LDON gear. Your best bet would be PoP pottery items. The Imporved Damage IV, Improved Healing IV, Spell Haste IV, and Extended Range IV are still infinitly useful and excellent to have to swap out. Get ready for sick farming tho &gt;&lt;
<br />

<br />
I like Daedallus idea about being able to select your adventure. I am sure lots would. No more rescue or collect please &gt;&lt; Which I am sure why they dont do it &gt;&lt; People could sit there and rack up the points, high slaughter plz~! WUWU.
<br />

<br />
But Ill still stand that LDON is one of the best expansions that have been put out. And it works for the most part, with varing content, great loot and its good for people who play casual or hardcore.
