                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">What I would like to see is a lower aggro but RESITABLE Tash that debuffs more magic than Tash.
<br />

<br />
I think it is absurd that mages and shaman can debuff Magic more than we can while also debuffing 3-4 others things at the same time.  It makes Tash look prett lame.
<br />

<br />
<ul>Resistable Tash
<br />
Less Aggro
<br />
More MR reduction
<br />
Does not replace what we have, but adds a logical set of spells to our lineup which is congruent with what Shaman have, which is a resistable version and an unresitable version.</ul>
<br />

<br />
Our best 60+ version of this new resistible Tash would debuff magic by over 100.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Mezrin Kortex</span> 65 Coercer <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=605959" target="_blank" class="postlink">Profile</a>
