                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">if a person is still lv 52 after 4 years of playing, they don't have an interest in raid encounters, and i don't think the Devs should spend all that much time develing such content for them. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Get with the program. EQ is becoming a mass market product aimed at volume. If SOE wants to really rake in the $$$ they should ONLY create content for casual gamers and family guilders. 
<br />

<br />
For players just joining the world EQ can be BLEAK. The focus on raiders and uber guilds have left the majority of the zones totally empty and has not created an inviting world experience for truly new customers.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Lvl 56 Necro
<br />
Lvl 51 Druid
