        <tr>
                <td class="spaceRow" colspan="2" height="1"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/spacer.gif" alt="" width="1" height="1" /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
		<td width="150" align="left" valign="top" class="row1"><a name="7899"></a><span class="name"><span class="usercolor">Axterix EnObelix</span></span><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_offline.gif" border="0" align="absbottom" alt="Offline" title="Offline" /><div class="gensmall"><img src="images/ranks/rank_7.gif" alt="Coercer" title="Coercer" border="0" /><br />Coercer</div><div align="left" class="gensmall">Joined:&nbsp;12 Aug 2003</div><div align="left" class="gensmall">Total posts:&nbsp;217</div><div align="left" class="gensmall">Gender:&nbsp;Unknown</div></td>
                <td class="row1" width="100%" height="28" valign="top"><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                        <tr>
                                <td width="100%"><a href="viewtopic.php?p=7899&amp;sid=c77e79d9351ebb6bbaf08ad53695881d#7899"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails">Posted: Fri Oct 17, 2003 8:53 pm<span class="gen">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;Post subject: </span></td>
                                <td valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=7899&amp;sid=c77e79d9351ebb6bbaf08ad53695881d"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>   </td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Daedallus wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">the small "family" oriented guilds don't need more to do, there is already content in abundance for them, the problem is not that there is nothing for them to do, its that the drive to do them isn't there. my girlfriend is in just such a guild. and they waste the content evailable to to them with apathy. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
This has a lot to do with mudflation...part of why I want all gear to have a required level.  They waste some of it with apathy, because there isn't a point.  But a lot of it is never up.  Killed by a few ubers who are bored, just want to test what they can do, or whatever.  And they can do this at any time, unlike a guild of casual players which must plan.
<br />

<br />
You try planning ahead some time...you try to say that on Saturday, 2 weeks from now, you're going to kill the va'dyn.
<br />

<br />
There's also the fact that they've basically been raised to not think about it.  A lot of EQ's play conditions serve to sap the drive to do the occassional raid.  Just because the game is that way doesn't justify keeping it that way.  I'd say the exact opposite.  That because those conditions exist, things should be added to encourage and facilitate a bit of raiding for those people.
<br />

<br />
As to loot items, CoF drops off talendor and a few other sources.  LDoN has a 36% haste aug.  People do the older stuff because it's easy.  Stick that same stuff in a level restricted mini-zone and make it no drop...it gets left alone for those that shouldn't be bothering with it.
<br />

<br />
Does it suck to lose content?  Sure.  About as much as it sucks to not be able to get to content.  You lose a little content that, frankly, you won't miss.  Although ideally, it'd be mini-zones that exist just for the purpose of the raid.  In return you gain new content that is useful.  You want to stroke your ego, do so on some tough non-raid mobs.  Plenty out there.  Think about players and their levels/drive.  It's basically a pyramid.  There's more people wanting it now than then.  Yet no more supply down low.  And you're saying yes, the top of that pyramid should be able to go back and slaughter that limited resource with even less people, considerably less organizational hassles.  Bad idea.
<br />

<br />
Which again will be nice when instancing is carried back a bit and to it's logical conclusion.  As long as loot is properly level limited and no drop, there will be a reason to do it, you will be able to plan when to do it.  Instanced takes care of your need to stroke your ego as well.  You can do so without bothering anyone although it should be rigged up in such a way that you can't use it to twink either.
<br />

<br />
But in any case, some new lower level raid content would be a very good thing.  It's what casual players were hoping for when they heard there would be raids in LDoN.  Instead, once again, it got catered just to the ubers.  Soon, we'll get 2 more LDoN raids.  Will any of it be targetted for lower levels, the huge number of people that would love to have access to such raids?  Nope.  And that needs to change.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>fimbul wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">For players just joining the world EQ can be BLEAK. The focus on raiders and uber guilds have left the majority of the zones totally empty and has not created an inviting world experience for truly new customers.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
And this is why.  I want people to feel that they don't have to rush to level.  I want the designers of EQ to feel that they don't have to make it easier and easier to level.  I want people joining today to feel the thrill of Sol B that I had, to take a year to get to 50 or 60.  To have a reason to go there.  Not to see the zone revamped.  Not to see them blitzing to 65 in a year or less.  And along that route, I want interesting things for them to do.  I want some of that feel from back then preserved, so that these areas aren't trivial and the bazaar isn't the best way to get gear.  Likewise, when playing a twink, I want new experiences for me to do.
<br />

<br />
It'd make a better game for all levels, instead of spending a huge chunk of resources solely on a tiny demographic that will never be satisfied.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
